Cyril Ramaphosa Photographer: Jerome Delay/AFP via Getty Images Photographer: Jerome Delay/AFP via Getty Images Sign up to our Next Africa newsletter and  follow Bloomberg Africa on Twitter South African President Cyril Ramaphosa will address the nation on Thursday on developments in the country’s strategy to manage the spread of Covid-19. The president’s address follows a number of meetings of the cabinet and the National Coronavirus Command Council, the presidency said in an emailed statement. Ramaphosa’s statement will be broadcast live at 8 p.m. on television and radio and will be streamed live on a range of online platforms.